flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.
It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.
It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.
It excels at digging holes. Using its ears, it can dig a nest 33 feet deep in one night.
It has a psychic power that enabled it to distort the space around it and see into the future.
With power equal to an excavator, it can dig through dense bedrock. It's a huge help during tunnel construction.
It grows dispirited if it is not with kind people. It can float in midair without moving its wings.
When it needs to think, it rotates its head 180 degrees to sharpen its intellectual power.
This Pokémon may be rude, but it takes very good care of its family, its friends, and its turf.
It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can't move as well.
It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.
When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.
It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.
As everyone knows, it visits peaceful regions, bringing them gifts of kindness and sweet blessings.
The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
This nuisance sneaks into people's homes, where it hides important things and scatters cotton all over the place.
It uses its tail to absorb electricity from power plants or from outlets in houses, and then it fires the electricity from its whiskers.
This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.
When this legendary Pokémon's wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.
By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.
When it sees a person, it digs a hole with its tail to make its escape. If you happen to find one, consider yourself lucky.
Its fluffy fur is a delight to pet, but carelessly reaching out to touch this Pokémon could result in painful retaliation.
To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can't move as well.
It's not safe without the power of a flower, but it will keep traveling around until it finds one with the color and shape it wants.
Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.
This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.
The way it brushes away grime with its tail can be helpful when cleaning. But its focus on spotlessness can make cleaning more of a hassle.
Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.
It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.
This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.
Although this Pokémon is not especially rare, its glittering, jewel-draped body draws attention from people.
Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.
It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!
It's not safe without the power of a flower, but it will keep traveling around until it finds one with the color and shape it wants.
Its body secretes oil that this Pokémon spreads over its nest as a coating to protect it from dust. Cinccino won't tolerate even a speck of the stuff.
Said to be the embodiment of north winds, it can instantly purify filthy, murky water.
This extremely rare Pokémon is a different color than usual. It is very hard to find.
It is thought that Uxie, Mesprit, and Azelf all came from the same egg.
Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous—it could easily shatter your bones.
When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.
This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.
In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.
Found throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon becomes uneasy if its cheeks are ever completely empty of berries.
It raises flowers and uses them as weapons. The more gorgeous the blossom, the more power it contains.
From its mouth, it fires the seeds of berries it has eaten. The scattered seeds give rise to new plants.
Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.
Myriads of Cutiefly flutter above the heads of people who have auras resembling those of flowers.
It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.
It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.
Some of Ribombee's pollen puffs are highly nutritious. They are sometimes sold as supplements.
It controls the flowers it grows. The petal blizzards that Florges triggers are overwhelming in their beauty and power.
It stashes berries in its tail—so many berries that they fall out constantly. But this Pokémon is a bit slow-witted, so it doesn't notice the loss.
Known for forming harmonious couples, this Pokémon is brought to wedding ceremonies as a good luck charm.
This legendary Pokémon is said to freeze the water in the air during winter, causing snow.
To protect itself, it shoots cotton from its body. When it gets wet in the rain, its cotton grows moist and heavy, and it can't move as well.
It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.
This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.
It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.
As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.
It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.
The flames on this legendary Pokémon's wings burn so brightly that they can make night seem like day.
Its incisors grow continuously throughout its life. If its incisors get too long, this Pokémon becomes unable to eat, and it starves to death.
It will bravely challenge any opponent, no matter how powerful. This Pokémon benefits from every battle—even a defeat increases its strength a bit.
It is highly popular among female Trainers for its sublime fur. It does not keep a nest.
This nuisance sneaks into people's homes, where it hides important things and scatters cotton all over the place.
This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.
As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.
To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.
It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.
People say that it fled from its enemies by using its small webbed hind feet to swim from island to island in Alola.
It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.
It sneaks into people's homes and steals electricity from their outlets. When your electric bill seems off, it's the handiwork of this rascal.
This legendary Pokémon is said to be present wherever there is a lightning storm.
By expelling water from the nozzle in the back of its claw, it can move at a speed of 60 knots.
Smart enough to use tools in battle, these Pokémon have been seen picking up rocks and flinging them or using ropes to wrap up enemies.
It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.
Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.
It is said to be able to seize anything it desires with its six rings and six huge arms. With its power sealed, it is transformed into a much smaller form.
Once a fight breaks out, it will unflinchingly charge at dragon Pokémon that are many times larger than itself.
Its reckless nature leads it to stand up to others—even large Pokémon—if it has to protect its territory.
If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.
A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.
Carrying food through Fearow's territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!
It's still weak, so it lurks on the floor of bodies of water, eating whatever food sinks down and living a quiet life.
Its curly fleece is such an effective cushion that this Pokémon could fall off a cliff and stand right back up at the bottom, unharmed.
As it flutters about, it scatters its strangely glowing scales. Touching them is said to restore good health on the spot.
They flock around mountains and fields, chasing after bug Pokémon. Their singing is noisy and annoying.
